TITLE: Implementing Uncontrolled ConnectModal Component in React
DESCRIPTION: Example of using ConnectModal without explicit state management. This implementation lets the component manage its own open/closed state internally, simplifying usage when external control is not needed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/ts-sdks/blob/main/packages/docs/content/dapp-kit/wallet-components/ConnectModal.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { ConnectModal, useCurrentAccount } from '@mysten/dapp-kit';

export function YourApp() {
	const currentAccount = useCurrentAccount();

	return (
		<ConnectModal
			trigger={
				<button disabled={!!currentAccount}> {currentAccount ? 'Connected' : 'Connect'}</button>
			}
		/>
	);
}
```

