TITLE: BCS Enum Type Handling in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the updated TypeScript types for BCS enum types, introducing the $kind property for variant discrimination.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mystenlabs/ts-sdks/blob/main/packages/docs/content/typescript/migrations/sui-1.0.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const MyEnum = bcs.enum('MyEnum', {
	Variant0: bcs.u16(),
	Variant1: bcs.u8(),
	Variant2: bcs.string(),
});

const parsed = MyEnum.deserialize(data);

// Discriminate using the $kind property
if (parsed.$kind === 'Variant0') {
	parsed.Variant0; // type is number
}

// We can also directly the enum properties
if (parsed.Variant0 !== undefined) {
	parsed.Variant0; // type is number
}
```

